Professor Adam Habib shares his thoughts on leaving Wits at the end of 2020. He will take up the position of Director at the School of Oriental and African Studies (SOAS) in London. He will join SOAS in 2021. JOHANNESBURG - University of Witwatersrand Vice-Chancellor Professor Adam Habib has announced his resignation from the institution. In a statement released on Tuesday, Habib said his decision to step down was not made lightly. He will officially leave the university at the end of December 2020. Habib is expected to take up the position of Director at the School of Oriental and African Studies in London.